        "column_hMCta8": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "title": "",
            "text": "<p>Like all new M Series wheelsets, the M6’s rims feature unique front and rear rim design. To accommodate the modern trail rider’s preference for 2.3-2.5” wide tires, the M6’s front rim features an internal rim width of 32mm, and the rear is 29mm. The front rim’s additional width and lighter construction maximize compliance, traction, and tire stability. The rear rim has been optimized for power transmission and durability.</p>",
            "link_label": "",
            "link": ""
          }
        },
        "column_Na6DLn": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "title": "",
            "text": "<p>In addition to the new rim design, the M6 is built to ENVE’s straight-pull INNERDRIVE mountain bike hubs. INNERDRIVE improves ratchet-driven technologies by increasing the diameter of the ratchets, which allows for higher engagement without sacrificing durability. Riders can choose between a 40, 60, 80 (stock offering), and 100t drive ratchet to tune the wheel to their preferences. Further benefits of the INNERDRIVE system include ENVE’s Perfect Preload system which delivers prolonged bearing life and minimal maintenance.<br/><br/></p>",
            "link_label": "",
            "link": ""
          }
        },
        "column_EWz7K8": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "title": "",
            "text": "<p>When considering E-MTB applications and compatibility, the M6 is an excellent choice for E-MTB riders looking to shed weight and improve the ride experience on light e-MTBs with peak torque ratings of 75 NM or less.</p>",
            "link_label": "",
            "link": ""
          }
        }
      },
